definition: to bring one's own/BYO/(of software) preinstalled

sentences.english: Bring your own healthy entrée or appetizer to the party.
sentences.chinese: 自带你的健康主食或者开胃菜去聚会。

sentences.english: Bring your own snacks and pack a brown-bag lunch to reduce costs even more.
sentences.chinese: 带自己的零食，自带午餐，来更多地减少成本。

sentences.english: There is corkage fee for brought in liquors.

sentences.english: Can be installed or custom built non-return valve function of the valve.
sentences.chinese: 可安装止回阀或订制自带止回功能的阀。

sentences.english: It is much cheaper to buy cash-and-carry.
sentences.chinese: 现金购物自带回家便宜多了。

sentences.english: The distribution kit includes more than 70 frames. Framing Studio contains flexible printing options.
sentences.chinese: 软件自带超过70种像框，而且打印功能也很灵活。

sentences.english: Some fittings and equipment have built-flange, flange connection also belongs.

sentences.english: The restaurant didn't have a liquor licence, but they allowed you to brown bag.
sentences.chinese: 那家馆子没有酒牌，不过允许客人自带酒水。

sentences.english: He always brown-bagged his lunch,unlike other executives.
sentences.chinese: 他总是用棕色纸袋自带午饭上班，不像其他管理人员。

sentences.english: Another quick feature this app comes with is the capturing of screenshots.

sentences.chinese: 我到中山路的新华书店都自带蜡烛，以备断电后使用。

sentences.english: Some restaurants allow you to take your own wine and just charge you corkage.
sentences.chinese: 有些餐厅允许顾客自带酒水，只收些开瓶费。

sentences.english: Self-contained dust extracting filter system, environmental protection and energy saving.
